=head1 DESCRIPTION

Contains details about the storage configuration of the knowledge base
in Pinecone. For more information, see Create a vector index in
Pinecone
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/knowledge-base-setup-pinecone.html).

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> ConnectionString => Str

The endpoint URL for your index management page.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> CredentialsSecretArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the secret that you created in
Secrets Manager that is linked to your Pinecone API key.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> FieldMapping => L<Paws::BedrockAgent::PineconeFieldMapping>

Contains the names of the fields to which to map information about the
vector store.


=head2 Namespace => Str

The namespace to be used to write new data to your database.



